# Biography

Erika Hutt, MD is an internist and current cardiovascular medicine fellow at the Cleveland Clinic. She was born and raised in Costa Rica, where she studied medicine at Universidad de Costa Rica. Her interest in clinical research led her to pursue medical training in the United States. She is currently a student of the Clinical Research Masters at Case Western University and she will be starting advanced cardiac imaging fellowship at Cleveland Clinic in July 2022. 
Her current area of research interest is in cardiac sarcoidosis and other infiltrative cardiomyopathies. 
During her free time, Erika enjoys cycling, hiking and spending time with friends and family. 

